<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,151,1083]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,915,939]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[562,649,915,939]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">syntype</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName authority="Melichar" authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1903" box="[770,1094,914,939]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biplagiata">
<emphasis box="[770,979,915,939]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Agallia biplagiata</emphasis>
Melichar
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1916" box="[1110,1348,914,939]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="campbelli">
<emphasis box="[1110,1256,915,939]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. campbelli</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janaka">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. janaka</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
clearly indicated that they are conspecific. This is a very widely distributed species in south 
<collectingCountry box="[1378,1435,950,974]" name="India" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[197,307,986,1010]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
with considerable variation in color. Coloration of male tends to be darker than in female. It was generally collected on grass mixed with dicotyledenous plants. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1903" box="[839,990,1022,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biplagiata">
<emphasis box="[839,990,1022,1046]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">H. biplagiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1121,1237,1022,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hemagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plotina">
<emphasis box="[1121,1237,1022,1046]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">H. plotina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in coloration but differs in having an arrowhead shaped aedeagal tip compared to a simple tip of the aedeagus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1221,1334,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hemagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plotina">
<emphasis box="[1221,1334,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">H. plotina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
